<HEADLINE>
FT  13 JAN 93 / Mozer charged after plea bargain fails
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PATRICK HARVERSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
MR PAUL MOZER, former head bond trader at Wall Street brokerage house
Salomon Brothers and the central figure in the 1991 Treasury auction
scandal, was indicted by federal prosecutors last night on a variety of
criminal charges.
This follows a judge's decision to reject a plea agreement drawn up by Mr
Mozer's lawyers and the government on the grounds that there were still too
many issues outstanding for a guilty plea to be accepted. After the
rejection, prosecutors drew up the new indictment, which charges Mr Mozer
with securities fraud, two counts of making false statements to Treasury
officials, and one of preparing false books and records.
