<HEADLINE>
FT  13 JAN 93 / Drinks tax plea
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE Wine and Spirits Association and the British Retail Consortium yesterday
urged the government to ease taxes on wines and spirits to combat the threat
of cross-Channel shopping to UK drinks retailers.
At a pre-Budget meeting with the Treasury they also called for a cut in the
tax on spirits and a freeze on wine duties.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
