FT  13 JAN 93 / Sense of financial security ebbs
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
FOUR in 10 Britons feel less financially secure than they did two years ago,
according to a survey published yesterday. The main reasons cited are fear
of unemployment and the effect of increased prices on those with low
incomes.
The Mori survey, conducted for the insurance company Scottish Amicable, also
found that Britons felt less financially secure than the French or Germans.
Mori interviewed 2,017 adults in Britain, 1,000 in France and 1,028 in
Germany. The interviews were conducted in September.
