<HEADLINE>
FT  13 JAN 93 / World Commodities Prices: Market Report
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
COPPER prices ended an active and volatile LME session weak, but above the
lows of a wide range. Copper also unsettled the other metals, which closed
lower. Dealers said the steep falls in copper, following Monday's decline,
reflected heavy Chinese selling that became a deluge of long liquidation and
speculative sales as the market's recent uptrend came to a halt. Some GOLD
dealers on the London bullion market saw news that the Dutch central bank
sold 400 tonnes last year as slightly bullish. 'If a substantial element of
it went to the market, then it may well be felt that the market held up
surprisingly well,' one dealer said. On Comex gold futures were firmer in
late trading but below the key Dollars 330 a troy ounce level breached
earlier. London COCOA futures finished with gains of up to Pounds 16 a tonne
with the market boosted by the weakness of sterling against other leading
currencies. Dealers said Ivorian sellers' were further from the market
following the pound's slump.
Compiled from Reuters
