FT  12 JAN 93 / UK Company News: British Sugar calls off talks to buy stake
in San Francisco refiner
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MAGGIE URRY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
British Sugar, the beet processing and marketing division of Associated
British Foods, has called off talks to buy a stake in a San Francisco-based
cane sugar refiner.
The discussions with Californian and Hawaiian Sugar Refinery, which were
disclosed in March last year, appear to have failed over the price British
Sugar was prepared to pay.
C&amp;H is a co-operative owned by the Hawaiian cane sugar growers who send
their raw cane to the refinery for processing and distribution. It is the
leading brand of sugar in the west of the US.
However, C&amp;H's co-operative status meant that all the growers had to agree
the deal and this seems to have proved impossible.
C&amp;H would have been British Sugar's first non-UK investment apart from two
factories it owns in Poland.
